library(haven)
library(readxl)
# Ler a base
itpd <- read_dta("itpd.dta")
# Remover com√©rcio dom√©stico e deixar a trade em bilh√µes
itpd <- itpd %>% 
  filter(exporter_iso3 != importer_iso3) %>% 
  mutate(trade = trade / 1000)

# Exporta√ß√µes totais por ind√∫stria por pa√≠s
itpd <- itpd %>% 
  group_by(exporter_iso3, industry_id) %>% 
  mutate(export_industry = sum(trade)) %>% 
  ungroup()
itpd <- itpd %>% 
  group_by(exporter_iso3, year) %>% 
  mutate(total_export_country = sum(trade)) %>% # Exporta√ß√µes totais por ano por pa√≠s
  group_by(exporter_iso3, year, industry_id) %>% 
  mutate(advantage = sum(trade) / total_export_country) # Vantagem absoluta por ind√∫stria por pa√≠s por ano
itpd <- itpd %>% 
  group_by(year) %>% 
  mutate(total_export_year = sum(trade)) %>% # Exporta√ß√µes totais por ano
  group_by(year, industry_id) %>% 
  mutate(total_export_year_industry = sum(trade)) %>% # Exporta√ß√µes totais por ano por ind√∫stria
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(rca = advantage / (total_export_year_industry / total_export_year)) # RCA por ind√∫stria por pa√≠s por ano
countries <- c("ARG", "BRA", "CHL", "VEN", "PRY", "URY", "COL", "BOL", "PER", "ECU")

theme_set(theme_minimal())

# Fun√ß√£o para fazer gr√°ficos das top 10 ind√∫strias de cada um dos pa√≠ses em diferentes anos
top_industries <- function(x) {
  itpd %>%
    select(exporter_iso3, industry_id, rca, year) %>%
    filter(year == x & exporter_iso3 %in% countries)  %>%
    distinct() %>%
    group_by(exporter_iso3) %>%
    arrange(desc(rca)) %>%
    slice_head(n = 10) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    split(.$exporter_iso3) %>%
    lapply(function(df) {
      ggplot(df, aes(x = reorder(factor(industry_id), rca), y = rca, 
                   fill = reorder(factor(industry_id), rca))) +
        geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
        coord_flip() +
        labs(
        y = "RCA",
        x = "Ind√∫stria",
        fill = "Industry ID",
        title = paste("Top 10 ind√∫strias por RCA para", unique(df$exporter_iso3), "em", x)
        ) +
        theme(legend.position="none")
  })
}

  filter(year > 1999)
# Ler a base WDI
wdi <- read_csv("wdi.csv", show_col_types = FALSE)

# Deixar a base no formato tidy apenas com √°rea agricultural
wdi_data <- wdi %>% 
  filter(indicatorcode == "AG.LND.AGRI.K2") %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = v1960:v2020, names_to = "year", values_to = "ag_lnd") %>% 
  mutate(year = as.numeric(str_extract(year, "\\d+"))) %>% 
  filter(year > 1999) %>% 
  reframe(countrycode, year, ag_lnd)
# Selecionar as vari√°veis de interesse da base ITPD
itpd_data <- itpd %>%
  select(exporter_iso3, year, industry_id, broad_sector, rca) %>% 
  distinct() %>% 
  rename("countrycode" = "exporter_iso3")

# Juntar as bases
data <- left_join(itpd_data, wdi_data, by = (c("countrycode", "year")))
data <- left_join(data, pwt, by = (c("countrycode", "year")))

# Fun√ß√£o para fazer binned scatter plot de cada setor
scatter <- function(col, title) {
  ggplot(data_2016, aes(x = !!enquo(col), y = log(rca))) + 
  geom_bin2d(bins=20) +
  stat_smooth(method = "lm",
              formula = y ~ x,
              geom = "smooth", 
              color = "red", 
              fill = "coral") +
  labs(x = title, y = "Log do RCA") +  
  guides(fill=guide_legend(title="Observa√ß√µes")) +
  facet_wrap(~broad_sector)
}

# Ler a base WDICountry e selecionar a renda
wdi_data <- read_xlsx("WDICountry.xlsx") %>% 
  rename("countrycode" = "Code", 
         "income" = "Income group") %>% 
  select(countrycode, income)

data <- itpd %>%
  filter(year == 2016) %>% # Deixar apenas o ano de 2016
  select(exporter_iso3, importer_iso3, industry_id, broad_sector, trade) %>%
  pivot_longer( # Deixar a base com apenas 1 pa√≠s por observa√ß√£o
    cols = c(exporter_iso3, importer_iso3),
    names_to = "type",
    values_to = "countrycode"
  ) %>%
  group_by(countrycode, type, industry_id) %>%
  mutate(industry_trade = sum(trade)) %>% # Valor de importa√ß√£o e exporta√ß√£o por ind√∫stria por pa√≠s
  select(-trade) %>%
  distinct() %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = type, values_from = industry_trade) %>% # Colocar o valor de importa√ß√£o e exporta√ß√£o em cada linha
  left_join(wdi_data, by = "countrycode") %>% # Pegar a renda dos pa√≠ses
  rename(
    "export" = "exporter_iso3",
    "import" = "importer_iso3"
  ) %>%
  group_by(countrycode, industry_id) %>%
  mutate(gl = 1 - (abs(export - import) / (export + import))) %>% # Fazer o √≠ndice gl
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(
    service = fct_recode(as.factor(broad_sector), # Transformar setor em fator de servi√ßo ou n√£o
      "N√£o-servi√ßos" = "1", "N√£o-servi√ßos" = "2",
      "N√£o-servi√ßos" = "3", "Servi√ßos" = "4"
    ),
    income = fct_recode(as.factor(income), # Transformar renda em fator de alto ou n√£o
      "Renda n√£o-alta" = "Low income", "Renda n√£o-alta" = "Lower middle income",
      "Renda alta" = "Upper middle income", "Renda alta" = "High income"
    )
  ) %>% 
  drop_na(income, service)
bins_fd <- function(vec) {
  as.integer(diff(range(vec, na.rm = T)) / (2 * IQR(vec, na.rm = T) / length(vec)^(1/3)))
} # Fun√ß√£o de freedman diaconis

data %>% # Histograma por setor e renda
  ggplot(aes(x = gl, y = ..density..)) +
    geom_histogram(bins = bins_fd(data$gl), color = "white", fill = "blue") + 
    labs(x = "√çndice de Grubel and Lloyd", y = "Densidade") +
    facet_grid(vars(income), vars(service))
